Description¶

This notebook brings together the notebooks for RNN and LinCRF.

The objective is to find out how different models behave on the extraction, which parameters and ensembles to use.

Given:

  • Simple NN
  • Complex NN
  • RNN
  • Random Forest (RF)
  • Feature sets A (190 features) and B (150 features)

Test:

  • Effects of undersampling unassigned elements during training
  • For 20% undersampling, test effects of using feature set A and B (on Simple NN, RNN, RF)
  • Postprocessing
    • precision/recall threshold adjustment
    • inst max
    • inst max per plabel
    • exclude author combinations

def print_full(x, cols=None):
    pd.set_option('display.max_rows', len(x))
    if cols:
        print(x[cols])
    else:
        print(x)
    pd.reset_option('display.max_rows')

%matplotlib inline
from sklearn.metrics import precision_recall_curve, auc, f1_score

def pr_curve(y, preds):
    plt.clf()
    for i, f in enumerate(['title','author','date','unassigned']):
        prec, rec, thresh = precision_recall_curve(y==i, preds[:,i])
        f1 = (2*(prec*rec)/(prec+rec))
        bestf1 = f1.argmax()
        t = thresh[f1.argmax()]
        auc_ = auc(rec, prec)
        
        plt.plot(rec,prec, label=f)
        
        if 0 < i < 3:
            displacex = 0.1 if i == 1 else 0.02
            displacey = 0.2

            plt.annotate('F1:{:.2}\nAUC: {:.2}\nT: {:.2}'.format(f1[bestf1],auc_,t),
                        xy=(rec[bestf1],prec[bestf1]),
                        xytext=(rec[bestf1]-displacex,prec[bestf1]-displacey),
                        arrowprops=dict(arrowstyle="->"),
                        ha='right',
                        va='top')
        if i == 0:
            plt.annotate('F1:{:.2}\nAUC: {:.2}\nT: {:.2}'.format(f1[bestf1],auc_,t),
                         xy=(rec[bestf1],prec[bestf1]),
                         xytext=(rec[bestf1]+0.05,prec[bestf1]),
                         arrowprops=dict(arrowstyle="->"),
                         ha='left')

    plt.ylabel('Precision')
    plt.xlabel('Recall')
    plt.ylim(0,1.1)
    plt.xlim(0,1.1)
    plt.legend(loc='upper left', bbox_to_anchor=(1.05, 1))
    plt.grid()
    plt.show()

from sklearn.metrics import precision_recall_curve
def doeval(pred, ytst, frm, raw, cnt):
    fram = eva.get_predictframe(pred, global_idxmax=True, plabel_idxmax=True, testfrm=frm)

    print('raw')
    eva.measure_performance(None, ytst, pred)
    #print('idxmax')
    #eva.measure_performance(None, y_testa, list(fram['gilabel']))
    #print('plabel idxmax')
    #eva.measure_performance(None, y_testa, list(fram['ilabel']))

    pr_curve(ytst, pred)

    ps = pd.Series([3]*len(fram), index=fram.index)

    prec, rec, thresh = precision_recall_curve(ytst==0, pred[:,0])
    f1 = (2*(prec*rec)/(prec+rec))
    bestf1 = np.nanargmax(f1)
    t = thresh[bestf1]
    print(t)
    ps.loc[list(fram[fram['title']>t].groupby('instance').idxmax()['title'])] = 0

    prec, rec, thresh = precision_recall_curve(ytst==1, pred[:,1])
    f1 = (2*(prec*rec)/(prec+rec))
    bestf1 = np.nanargmax(f1)
    t = thresh[bestf1]
    print(t)
    cnt_frm_ = cnt_frm.loc[fram[(fram['author']>t)].index]
    ps.loc[fram[(fram['author']>t)&(cnt_frm_['score']<40)].index] = 1

    prec, rec, thresh = precision_recall_curve(ytst==2, pred[:,2])
    f1 = (2*(prec*rec)/(prec+rec))
    bestf1 = np.nanargmax(f1)
    t = thresh[bestf1]
    print(t)
    ps.loc[list(fram[(~raw['text'].str.contains(r'\d{4}.+?\d{4}'))&
           (~raw['text'].str.contains(r'(?:^|\D)\d{3}(?:\D|$)'))&
           (fram['issued']>t)].groupby('instance').idxmax()['issued'])] = 2

    eva.measure_performance(None, ytst, list(ps))
    return ps, fram

neighbourhood_size = 10

eva_a = eva_a + (eva_a[0].get_keep_features(),)
eva_a = eva_a + eva_a[0].get_traintest_i_flat(reduction_min=4, 
                                              reduction=unassigned_reduction)

eva_b = (Evaluator(feature_frame, mask, feature_weights_b),)

eva_b = eva_b + eva_b[0].get_traintest_i_flat(reduction_min=4, reduction=unassigned_reduction)

                                              reduction=0.6,
                                              testsetfix=list(set(test['instance'])))

    fs = []

        fs.append('\Phi^B')
    if len(fs) == 0:
        fs = ['-']

eva, keep_features, test, train, X_train, y_train, Y_train, X_test, y_test, Y_test, nb_classes, class_weights = eva_b
In [9]:
from keras.models import Sequential
from keras.layers.core import Dense, Activation, Dropout
from keras.layers.advanced_activations import LeakyReLU
from keras.regularizers import l2, activity_l2
from keras.utils import np_utils
from sklearn.multiclass import OneVsRestClassifier
import keras.optimizers as opts
from keras.callbacks import TensorBoard

nb_epoch = 25
batch_size = 10
val_data_size = 50

model_nn1 = Sequential()
model_nn1.add(Dense(output_dim=len(keep_features), input_dim=len(keep_features), init='he_uniform'))
model_nn1.add(Activation("linear"))

model_nn1.add(Dense(80, W_regularizer=l2(0.01), init='he_uniform'))
model_nn1.add(Activation("softsign"))
model_nn1.add(Dropout(0.4))

model_nn1.add(Dense(35, W_regularizer=l2(0.01), init='he_uniform'))
model_nn1.add(Activation("softsign"))
model_nn1.add(Dropout(0.2))

model_nn1.add(Dense(nb_classes, init='he_uniform'))
model_nn1.add(Activation("softmax"))

model_nn1.summary()

model_nn1.compile(loss='msle',
              optimizer=opts.Adadelta(),
              metrics=['accuracy'])

history_nn1 = model_nn1.fit(X_train, Y_train,
                    batch_size=batch_size, 
                    nb_epoch=nb_epoch,
                    class_weight=class_weights,
                    verbose=1, 
                    validation_data=(X_test[:val_data_size], Y_test[:val_data_size]))
print('done')

In [29]:
import re
cnts = []

for iinst, inst in  raw_framee.groupby('instance'):
    remove = r'[\.,\;\-\(\)&\'\"\%\:\\\|\/]'
    cnt = pd.Series(re.sub(r'\W+',' ', re.sub(remove,' '," ".join(list(inst['text'])).lower())).split(' ')).value_counts()

    for i, row in inst.iterrows():
        tc = 0
        for w in re.sub(r'\W+',' ', re.sub(remove,' ', row['text'].lower())).split(' '):
            if w in cnt.index and len(w)>1:
                tc = tc+cnt.loc[w]
        cnts.append({
                'label': row['label'],
                'score': tc,
                'inst': row['instance']
            })
cnt_frme = pd.DataFrame(cnts, index = raw_framee.index)
In [30]:
import re
cnts = []

for iinst, inst in  raw_frame.groupby('instance'):
    remove = r'[\.,\;\-\(\)&\'\"\%\:\\\|\/]'
    cnt = pd.Series(re.sub(r'\W+',' ', re.sub(remove,' '," ".join(list(inst['text'])).lower())).split(' ')).value_counts()

    for i, row in inst.iterrows():
        tc = 0
        for w in re.sub(r'\W+',' ', re.sub(remove,' ', row['text'].lower())).split(' '):
            if w in cnt.index and len(w)>1:
                tc = tc+cnt.loc[w]
        cnts.append({
                'label': row['label'],
                'score': tc,
                'inst': row['instance']
            })
cnt_frm = pd.DataFrame(cnts, index = raw_frame.index)

    #print(inst.shape)
    if inst.shape[0] > 1:
        for j in range(len(inst)-1):
            for k in range(j+1, len(inst)):
                a = feature_frame.loc[inst.iloc[j].name][['center_x','center_y']].as_matrix()
                b = feature_frame.loc[inst.iloc[k].name][['center_x','center_y']].as_matrix()
                if np.linalg.norm(a-b) < 250:
                    #if inst.iloc[j]['author'] > thr:
                    ps.loc[inst.iloc[j].name] = 1
                    #if inst.iloc[k]['author'] > thr:
                    ps.loc[inst.iloc[k].name] = 1
                else:
                    mx = np.argmax([inst.iloc[j]['author'], inst.iloc[k]['author']])
                    #if inst.iloc[[j,k][mx]]['author'] > thr:
                    ps.loc[[inst.iloc[j].name,inst.iloc[k].name][mx]] = 1
    else:
        #if inst.iloc[0]['author'] > thr:
        ps.loc[inst.iloc[0].name] = 1

from keras.models import Sequential
from keras.layers.core import Dense, Activation, Dropout
from keras.layers.wrappers import TimeDistributed
from keras.layers.recurrent import LSTM, SimpleRNN
from keras.callbacks import EarlyStopping, TensorBoard

from keras.layers.advanced_activations import LeakyReLU
from keras.regularizers import l2, activity_l2
from keras.utils import np_utils
import keras.optimizers as opts

nb_epoch = 20
batch_size = 20
val_data_size = 50

model_rnn = Sequential()

model_rnn.add(TimeDistributed(
            Dense(output_dim=len(keep_features), 
                  input_dim=len(keep_features), 
                  init='he_uniform',
                  activation='linear',
                  name='input_layer'
                 ), 
            input_shape=(neighbourhood_size, len(keep_features)),
            name='dist_in_layer'))

model_rnn.add(SimpleRNN(70, 
               return_sequences=True,
               activation='softsign',
               W_regularizer=l2(0.01), 
               U_regularizer=l2(0.01),
               dropout_U=0.5,
               dropout_W=0.2,
               init='he_uniform',
               name='rnn_layer1'
              ))

model_rnn.add(SimpleRNN(40,
               return_sequences=False,
               activation='softsign', 
               W_regularizer=l2(0.01), 
               U_regularizer=l2(0.01),
               dropout_U=0.3,
               dropout_W=0.1,
               init='he_uniform',
               name='rnn_layer2'
              ))

model_rnn.add(Dense(nb_classes,
                init='he_uniform',
                activation='softmax', 
                name='out_layer'))

model_rnn.summary()

print('compiling model...')
model_rnn.compile(loss='msle',
              optimizer=opts.Adadelta(),
              metrics=['accuracy'])

print('starting training...')
history = model_rnn.fit(X_train, Y_train,
                batch_size=batch_size, nb_epoch=nb_epoch,
                class_weight=class_weights,
                verbose=1,
                validation_data=(X_test[:val_data_size], Y_test[:val_data_size]))

print('done')

from sklearn.metrics import precision_recall_curve
ps = pd.Series([3]*len(predictframe_rnn), index=predictframe_rnn.index)

prec, rec, thresh = precision_recall_curve(y_test==0, predictions_rnn[:,0])
f1 = np.nan_to_num((2*(prec*rec)/(prec+rec)))
bestf1 = f1.argmax()

ps.loc[predictframe_rnn[(predictframe_rnn['plabel']==0)&
                        (predictframe_rnn['title']>=thresh[bestf1]-0.1) #np.argmax(rec<0.99)
                       ].groupby('instance').idxmax()['title']] = 0

prec, rec, thresh = precision_recall_curve(y_test==1, predictions_rnn[:,1])
f1 = np.nan_to_num((2*(prec*rec)/(prec+rec)))
bestf1 = f1.argmax()
r = thresh[bestf1]-0.1 #0.72
tmp = raw_frame.loc[predictframe_rnn[(predictframe_rnn['plabel']==1)&
                                     (predictframe_rnn['author']>r)].index]
cnt_frm_ = cnt_frm.loc[predictframe_rnn[(predictframe_rnn['plabel']==1)&
                                     (predictframe_rnn['author']>r)].index]

ps.loc[predictframe_rnn[(predictframe_rnn['plabel']==1)&
                        (predictframe_rnn['author']>r)&
                        (~tmp['text'].str.contains('sign',case=False))&
                        (~tmp['text'].str.contains('more',case=False))&
                        (~tmp['text'].str.contains('share',case=False))&
                        (~tmp['text'].str.contains('contact',case=False))&
                        (~tmp['text'].str.contains('news',case=False))&
                        (~tmp['text'].str.contains('the ',case=False))&
                        (~tmp['text'].str.contains('about ',case=False))
                       ].groupby('instance').idxmax()['author']] = 1

prec, rec, thresh = precision_recall_curve(y_test==2, predictions_rnn[:,2])
f1 = np.nan_to_num((2*(prec*rec)/(prec+rec)))
bestf1 = f1.argmax()

ps.loc[predictframe_rnn[(predictframe_rnn['plabel']==2)&
                        (~raw_frame['text'].str.contains(r'\d{4}.+?\d{4}'))&
                        (~raw_frame['text'].str.contains(r'(?:^|\D)\d{3}(?:\D|$)'))&
                        (predictframe_rnn['issued']>thresh[bestf1]-0.05)
                       ].groupby('instance').idxmax()['issued']] = 2

eva.measure_performance(None, y_test, list(ps))

from sklearn.multiclass import OneVsRestClassifier
from sklearn.ensemble import BaggingClassifier, RandomForestClassifier
import warnings

forest = RandomForestClassifier(class_weight='balanced', criterion='entropy', n_estimators=400, n_jobs=50)
bag = BaggingClassifier(forest, n_estimators=20, max_features=0.7, n_jobs=1)
clf = OneVsRestClassifier(bag, n_jobs=1)

with warnings.catch_warnings():
    warnings.simplefilter('ignore', DeprecationWarning)
    clf.fit(X_train, y_train)

from sklearn.metrics import precision_recall_curve
ps = pd.Series([3]*len(predictframe_merge), index=predictframe_merge.index)

prec, rec, thresh = precision_recall_curve(y_test==0, predictions_merge[:,0])
ps.loc[predictframe_merge['title']>thresh[np.argmax(prec>0.85)]] = 0

prec, rec, thresh = precision_recall_curve(y_test==1, predictions_merge[:,1])
f1 = (2*(prec*rec)/(prec+rec))
bestf1 = f1.argmax()
t = thresh[f1.argmax()]-0.05
r = 0.7
tmp = raw_frame.loc[predictframe_merge[#(predictframe_merge['plabel']==1)&
                                       #(predictframe_merge['author']>thresh[np.argmax(rec<r)])
                                       (predictframe_merge['author']>t)].index]
cnt_frm_ = cnt_frm.loc[predictframe_merge[#(predictframe_merge['plabel']==1)&
                                       #(predictframe_merge['author']>thresh[np.argmax(rec<r)])
                                       (predictframe_merge['author']>t)].index]
print(len(cnt_frm_))
print(tmp.shape)
ps.loc[predictframe_merge[
       #(predictframe_merge['plabel']==1)&
       #(predictframe_merge['author']>thresh[np.argmax(rec<r)])&
       (predictframe_merge['author']>t-0.1)& 
       #(feature_frame['num_words']>1)&
       #(~tmp['text'].str.contains('sign',case=False))&
       #(~tmp['text'].str.contains('more',case=False))&
       #(~tmp['text'].str.contains('share',case=False))&
       #(~tmp['text'].str.contains('contact',case=False))&
       #(~tmp['text'].str.contains('news',case=False))&
       #(~tmp['text'].str.contains('the ',case=False))&
       #(~tmp['text'].str.contains('about ',case=False))&
       (cnt_frm_['score']<40)].index
      ] = 1
print(ps[ps==1].shape)

prec, rec, thresh = precision_recall_curve(y_test==2, predictions_merge[:,2])
ps.loc[(~raw_frame['text'].str.contains(r'\d{4}.+?\d{4}'))&
       (~raw_frame['text'].str.contains(r'(?:^|\D)\d{3}(?:\D|$)'))&
       (predictframe_merge['issued']>thresh[np.argmax(rec<0.78)])] = 2
predictframe_merge['tf'] = ps

def getnums(i, inst, lab):
    return {
        'instance': i,
        'label': lab,
        'has': len(inst[inst['label']==lab]),
        'found': len(inst[inst['flab']==lab]), 
        'correct': len(inst[(inst['label']==lab)&(inst['flab']==lab)]),
        'diff': len(inst[((inst['label']!=lab)&(inst['flab']==lab))|
                         ((inst['label']==lab)&(inst['flab']!=lab))])
    }

tmp = []
for i, inst in predictframe_merge.groupby('instance'):
    print('==== inst {} ====='.format(i))
    ttmp = getnums(i, inst, 0)
    tmp.append(ttmp)
    print('TITLE  : has: {has}, found: {found}, correct: {correct}, diff: {diff}'.format(**ttmp))
    ttmp = getnums(i, inst, 1)
    tmp.append(ttmp)
    print('AUTHOR : has: {has}, found: {found}, correct: {correct}, diff: {diff}'.format(**ttmp))
    ttmp = getnums(i, inst, 2)
    tmp.append(ttmp)
    print('DATE   : has: {has}, found: {found}, correct: {correct}, diff: {diff}'.format(**ttmp))

allfrm = pd.DataFrame(tmp)

In [186]:
def getnums(i, inst, lab):
    return {
        'instance': i,
        'label': lab,
        'has': len(inst[inst['label']==lab]),
        'found': len(inst[inst['plabel']==lab]), 
        'correct': len(inst[(inst['label']==lab)&(inst['plabel']==lab)]),
        'diff': len(inst[((inst['label']!=lab)&(inst['plabel']==lab))|
                         ((inst['label']==lab)&(inst['plabel']!=lab))])
    }

tmp = []
for i, inst in predictframe_nn1.groupby('instance'):
    print('==== inst {} ====='.format(i))
    ttmp = getnums(i, inst, 0)
    tmp.append(ttmp)
    print('TITLE  : has: {has}, found: {found}, correct: {correct}, diff: {diff}'.format(**ttmp))
    ttmp = getnums(i, inst, 1)
    tmp.append(ttmp)
    print('AUTHOR : has: {has}, found: {found}, correct: {correct}, diff: {diff}'.format(**ttmp))
    ttmp = getnums(i, inst, 2)
    tmp.append(ttmp)
    print('DATE   : has: {has}, found: {found}, correct: {correct}, diff: {diff}'.format(**ttmp))

allfrmr = pd.DataFrame(tmp)

In [191]:
def getnums(i, inst, lab):
    return {
        'instance': i,
        'label': lab,
        'has': len(inst[inst['label']==lab]),
        'found': len(inst[inst['plabel']==lab]), 
        'correct': len(inst[(inst['label']==lab)&(inst['plabel']==lab)]),
        'diff': len(inst[((inst['label']!=lab)&(inst['plabel']==lab))|
                         ((inst['label']==lab)&(inst['plabel']!=lab))])
    }

tmp = []
for i, inst in predictframe_merge.groupby('instance'):
    print('==== inst {} ====='.format(i))
    ttmp = getnums(i, inst, 0)
    tmp.append(ttmp)
    print('TITLE  : has: {has}, found: {found}, correct: {correct}, diff: {diff}'.format(**ttmp))
    ttmp = getnums(i, inst, 1)
    tmp.append(ttmp)
    print('AUTHOR : has: {has}, found: {found}, correct: {correct}, diff: {diff}'.format(**ttmp))
    ttmp = getnums(i, inst, 2)
    tmp.append(ttmp)
    print('DATE   : has: {has}, found: {found}, correct: {correct}, diff: {diff}'.format(**ttmp))

allfrmm = pd.DataFrame(tmp)

def getnums(i, inst, lab):
    return {
        'instance': i,
        'label': lab,
        'has': len(inst[inst['label']==lab]),
        'found': len(inst[inst['flab']==lab]), 
        'correct': len(inst[(inst['label']==lab)&(inst['flab']==lab)]),
        'diff': len(inst[((inst['label']!=lab)&(inst['flab']==lab))|
                         ((inst['label']==lab)&(inst['flab']!=lab))])
    }

tmp = []
for i, inst in predictframe_mergee.groupby('instance'):
    print('==== inst {} ====='.format(i))
    ttmp = getnums(i, inst, 0)
    tmp.append(ttmp)
    print('TITLE  : has: {has}, found: {found}, correct: {correct}, diff: {diff}'.format(**ttmp))
    ttmp = getnums(i, inst, 1)
    tmp.append(ttmp)
    print('AUTHOR : has: {has}, found: {found}, correct: {correct}, diff: {diff}'.format(**ttmp))
    ttmp = getnums(i, inst, 2)
    tmp.append(ttmp)
    print('DATE   : has: {has}, found: {found}, correct: {correct}, diff: {diff}'.format(**ttmp))

allfrme= pd.DataFrame(tmp)

In [183]:
alph = "abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz"
def mengle(t):
    m = ''
    for c in t:
        if c.lower() in alph:
            rc = alph[np.random.randint(0,25)]
            m = m + (rc if c.islower() else rc.upper())
        elif c.isdigit():
            m = m + str(np.random.randint(0,9))
        else:
            m = m+c
    return m

#571
inst = 763
with open('/vol/www-vol4/mi09/repketim/.public_html/files/msc/jumble.html', 'w') as hf:
    hf.write('<html><head></head><body>')
    for i, r in raw_frame[mask&(raw_frame['instance']==inst)].iterrows():
        r=r.to_dict()
        r.update({'blabla':i})
        #if r['bounds_top']>850:
        #    r.update({'bounds_top':r['bounds_top']-370})
        r.update({'textt':mengle(r['text'])})
        hf.write(('<div style="position:absolute; '
                 'top:{bounds_top}px; '
                 'left:{bounds_left}px; '
                 'width:{bounds_width}px; '
                 'height:{bounds_height}; '
                 'padding: {padding_top} {padding_right} {padding_bottom} {padding_left}; ' 
                 'margin: {margin_top} {margin_right} {margin_bottom} {margin_left}; ' 
                 'font-size:{font_size}; '
                 'font-weight:{font_weight}; '
                 'font-style:{font_style}; '
                 'border: 1px dotted lightgray; '
                 'text-align: {text_align}; ' 
                 'background-color: {background_color};">{textt}</div>').format(**r))
    hf.write('<a href="{}" style="display:block; position:fixed; top:10.0px; left:10.0px; font-size:30px;">source</a>'.format(meta_frame.loc[inst]['url']))
    hf.write('</body></html>')

def prettyconfuse(frm):
    for (lab,met), nums in frm.iterrows():
        if met == 'mean':
            print('{lab:{width}}{0:{width}{base}}{1:{width}{base}}{2:{width}{base}}{3:{width}{base}}'\
              .format(int(np.round(nums['conf_t'])),int(np.round(nums['conf_a'])),
                      int(np.round(nums['conf_d'])),int(np.round(nums['conf_u'])),
                      lab=['Title','Author','Date','Unass'][lab],
                      base='d', width=7))
    return frm

def prettyclass(frm):
    wdth = 10
    print('{lab:{width}}{0:{width}}{1:{width}}{2:{width}}{3:{width}}'\
          .format('Precision', 'Recall', 'F1', 'Support', width=wdth, lab='Label'))
    for (lab,met), nums in frm.iterrows():
        if met == 'mean':
            print('{lab:{width}}{0:{width}}{1:{width}}{2:{width}}{3:{width}}'\
              .format(nums['precision'],nums['recall'],
                      nums['f1'],nums['support'],
                      lab=['Title','Author','Date','Unass'][lab],
                      width=wdth))
    return frm

import re
urls = [re.search(r'//(www\.)?(.+?)/', url, re.IGNORECASE).group(2) for url in list(meta_frame['url'])]
print('num urls gs:',len(urls))
print('num uniq TLDs ev: {} ({:.4}%)'.format(len(set(urls)),
                                             len(set(urls))/len(urls)*100))

urlse = [re.search(r'//(www\.)?(.+?)/', url, re.IGNORECASE).group(2) for url in list(meta_framee['url'])]
print('num urls ev:',len(urlse))
print('num uniq TLDs ev: {} ({:.4}%)'.format(len(set(urlse)),
                                             len(set(urlse))/len(urlse)*100))

print('num TLDs in ev not in gs: {} ({:.4}%)'.format(len(set(urlse)-set(urls)), 
                                                     100*len(set(urlse)-set(urls))/len(set(urlse))))

for tmp, tmp2 in [(
        evfrm[(evfrm['classifier']=='merge')&
              (((evfrm['method']=='thfmx')&(evfrm['label']!=1))|
               ((evfrm['method']=='thrfil')&(evfrm['label']==1)))&
              (evfrm['set']==0)],
        evfrm[(evfrm['classifier']=='merge')&
              (((evfrm['method']=='thfmx')&(evfrm['label']!=1))|
               ((evfrm['method']=='thrfil')&(evfrm['label']==1)))&
              (evfrm['set']==1)]
    ), (
        evfrm[(evfrm['classifier']=='merge')&
              (evfrm['method']=='thfmx')&
              (evfrm['set']==0)],
        evfrm[(evfrm['classifier']=='merge')&
              (evfrm['method']=='thfmx')&
              (evfrm['set']==1)]
    )]:
    f, axarr = plt.subplots(1,3, figsize=(14,5), squeeze=False)
    bp = axarr[0, 0].boxplot([tmp[tmp['label']==0][['precision']].as_matrix(),
                 tmp2[tmp2['label']==0][['precision']].as_matrix(),
                 tmp[tmp['label']==1][['precision']].as_matrix(),
                 tmp2[tmp2['label']==1][['precision']].as_matrix(),
                 tmp[tmp['label']==2][['precision']].as_matrix(),
                 tmp2[tmp2['label']==2][['precision']].as_matrix()],
                       labels=['Title (Test)', 'Title (Eval)',
                               'Author (Test)', 'Author (Eval)',
                               'Date (Test)', 'Date (Eval)'])
    axarr[0, 0].set_title('Precision')
    axarr[0, 0].set_ylim(0.2,1)
    axarr[0, 0].grid()
    plt.setp(bp['medians'], color='black')
    plt.setp(bp['boxes'], color='black')
    plt.setp(bp['fliers'], color='black')
    plt.setp(bp['whiskers'], color='black')
    
    bp = axarr[0, 1].boxplot([tmp[tmp['label']==0][['recall']].as_matrix(),
                 tmp2[tmp2['label']==0][['recall']].as_matrix(),
                 tmp[tmp['label']==1][['recall']].as_matrix(),
                 tmp2[tmp2['label']==1][['recall']].as_matrix(),
                 tmp[tmp['label']==2][['recall']].as_matrix(),
                 tmp2[tmp2['label']==2][['recall']].as_matrix()],
                       labels=['Title (Test)', 'Title (Eval)',
                               'Author (Test)', 'Author (Eval)',
                               'Date (Test)', 'Date (Eval)'])
    axarr[0, 1].set_title('Recall')
    axarr[0, 1].grid()
    axarr[0, 1].set_ylim(0.2,1)
    plt.setp(bp['medians'], color='black')
    plt.setp(bp['boxes'], color='black')
    plt.setp(bp['fliers'], color='black')
    plt.setp(bp['whiskers'], color='black')
    
    bp = axarr[0, 2].boxplot([tmp[tmp['label']==0][['f1']].as_matrix(),
                 tmp2[tmp2['label']==0][['f1']].as_matrix(),
                 tmp[tmp['label']==1][['f1']].as_matrix(),
                 tmp2[tmp2['label']==1][['f1']].as_matrix(),
                 tmp[tmp['label']==2][['f1']].as_matrix(),

                       labels=['Title (Test)', 'Title (Eval)',
                               'Author (Test)', 'Author (Eval)',
                               'Date (Test)', 'Date (Eval)'])
    axarr[0, 2].set_title('F1')
    axarr[0, 2].set_ylim(0.2,1)
    axarr[0, 2].grid()
    plt.setp(bp['medians'], color='black')
    plt.setp(bp['boxes'], color='black')
    plt.setp(bp['fliers'], color='black')
    plt.setp(bp['whiskers'], color='black')

    plt.setp(axarr[0, 1].get_xticklabels(), rotation=40, ha='right')
